The failure is a linking artifact, not a durability bug. `start_link` links the server to the test process. When the test does `Process.exit(pid, :kill)`, the untrappable `:killed` exit reason propagates across the link to the (non-trapping) test process, killing it — that's the `{:EXIT, #PID<...>}: :killed`. The recovery logic itself is fine. The fix is to `Process.unlink(pid)` before hard-killing it, so only the monitor observes the death.

